
dep.require 'hs.Template'

dep.provide 'hs.t.PrivacyPolicy'


class hs.t.PrivacyPolicy extends hs.Template

  appendTo: '#main'

  template: -> '''
    <div class="flatpage">
      <h1>Hipsell Inc. Privacy Policy</h1>

      <h3>Introduction</h3>
      <p>This Privacy Policy (the "Policy") describes the practices of Hipsell Inc. (“Hipsell”)  in connection with its collection, use and disclosure of Personal Information (as defined below). At Hipsell, we are committed to protecting your privacy through practices that limit the collection, use and disclosure of Personal Information to what is necessary for the intended purpose, including in respect of what is required to provide the Service to you and our other users. This Policy was created to inform you of our commitment to protecting your Personal Information and is based on the general principles in Schedule 1 of the federal Personal Information Protection and Electronic Documents Act (Canada).  This Policy only applies to Hipsell and not to any third party that you may access or communicate with utilizing the Service. </p>

      <h3>Definition of Personal Information</h3>
      <p>Personal Information includes any information about an identifiable individual. We receive and store any information you Transmit utilizing the Service or provide to us in any other way. The types of Personal Information collected may include your name, user name, address, email address, email contacts, phone number, birthday, gender, user information browser information, IP address, cookie information and your location. </p>

      <h3>Purpose for the collection and use of your Personal Information</h3>
      <p>The Personal Information we gather from users enables us to personalize and improve our services and to allow our users to set up a user account and profile that can be used to interact with other users through the Service. In connection with the Service, we request and display some Personal Information to other users and visitors of the Service, to enable users to identify each other.</p>
      <p>The Personal Information you provide is used for such purposes as allowing you to interact with other users, improving the content of the Service, developing and enhancing our product offerings, managing our business and operations, customizing the advertising and content you see, and communicating with you about specials and new features and administering your user account. We may also draw upon this Personal Information in order to adapt the Services, to research the effectiveness of our Service, and to develop new tools for the Services and new services. </p>
      <p>Hipsell also uses personal and other information and data that is collected in an aggregated and anonymized manner, as a statistical measure, and not in a manner that would identify you personally, to improve the Service, product offerings and to administer our business.  We reserve the right to use, disclose, sell, trade or rent data aggregated provided that such data is not linked to any specific individual. </p>
      <p>The Service allows you to connect with certain third party services. When you broadcast information to such third party services, such information is no longer under the control of Hipsell and is subject to the terms of use and privacy policies of such third parties. </p>

      <h3>Use and Disclosure of Personal Information</h3>
      <p>The Service is designed to help you share information, including your location, with others. You can control the disclosure of your personal information through your privacy settings. Information you submit to the Service will be available to users of the Service and third parties accessing the Service in accordance with the selected privacy settings. This is primarily so your friends can find you and send a meeting invitation. </p>
      <p>Please remember that if you choose to provide Personal Information using certain features of the Service, that information is governed by the privacy settings of those particular features and, unless selected otherwise, may be available to a broad group Hipsell users or may be published on the Hipsell website, which is subject to indexing by third party search engines. Individuals reading this information may use or disclose it to other individuals or entities without our control and without your knowledge. </p>
      <p>We enter into relationships with a variety of businesses and partners who we may share your Personal Information with, unless you have elected not to be solicited by marketing partners during the registration process or through the account settings page. These businesses may be in the business of selling or promoting goods or services and they may communicate with you or provide promotions to you through the Service.  Additionally, as part of the Service you may be exposed to offers from Hipsell on behalf of other businesses. However, in connection with such offers we do not give the other business your name, address, or email address.</p>
      <p>To be able to serve you, your Personal Information may be collected, stored and/or processed or otherwise used by or on our or your behalf both inside and outside of Canada by third party service providers or partners to perform certain functions. As a result, that country's courts, governments or law enforcement agencies could obtain disclosure of such Personal Information under that country's laws. These agents or service providers do not have any right to use your Personal Information we share with them beyond what is necessary to assist us.</p>
      <p>When you invite someone to join Hipsell, please be aware that we will disclose your real name, as an invitation containing your name will be sent to the email address of the person you wish to invite. </p>
      <p>Hipsell may also disclose your Personal Information as may be necessary in connection with operating our business, including as part of a sale or disposition of all or any portion of our business. In all such circumstances Hipsell will use commercially reasonable efforts to obtain an agreement from any potential purchaser to maintain the confidentiality of your Personal Information and only use it as permitted by law. Moreover, in the unlikely event that Hipsell goes out of business or enters bankruptcy, user information would be one of the assets that is transferred or acquired by a third party. You acknowledge that such transfers may occur, and that any acquirer of Hipsell or the assets of Hipsell may continue to use your Personal Information as set forth in this policy.</p>
      <p>We may release Personal Information when we believe in good faith that release is necessary to comply with any applicable law; enforce or apply our conditions of use and other agreements; or protect the rights, property, or safety of Hipsell, our employees, our users or others. </p>

      <h3>Consenting to Our Collection, Use and Disclosure of your Personal Information</h3>
      <p>The collection, use or disclosure of your Personal Information by Hipsell requires your knowledge and consent. At certain times, your consent for the collection, use and disclosure of your Personal Information may be implied from the manner in which it is collected.  Your consent may also be expressly provided by you. If Hipsell collects, uses or discloses Personal Information for purposes other than those described above, prior to the collection, use and/or disclosure of such Personal Information, unless required to be disclosed by law, you will be informed of, and your consent obtained prior to, Hipsell’s collection, use and/or disclosure of that Personal Information. If we intend to use and/or disclose Personal Information that we previously collected for a new purpose which is not authorized under applicable laws, your consent will always be obtained before we use and/or disclose it for that new purpose.</p>
      <p>There are certain situations defined by law where, Hipsell may or may be required to collect, use or disclose your Personal Information without your knowledge of or consent thereof. One example would be if Hipsell must disclose your Personal Information in order to comply with a subpoena or court order.</p>
      <p>You may always choose not to supply Hipsell with your Personal Information. However, if you choose not to supply us with your Personal Information, we may not provide you with the Service or it may impact our ability to offer you services or respond to your needs.</p>

      <h3>Retention of your Personal Information</h3>
      <p>Hipsell will retain your Personal Information for as long as it is necessary to fulfill the purpose for which it was collected and to comply with applicable laws. After the Personal Information is no longer necessary either for the purpose for which it was collected or to comply with any laws it will be destroyed, erased, or made anonymous in accordance with Hipsell’s document retention and destruction policies as in effect from time to time. You may revoke your consent to collect, use or disclose your Personal Information subject to applicable law and as may be required by Hipsell in connection with any legal obligation previously entered into in connection therewith.</p>

      <h3>Protection of your Personal Information.</h3>
      <p>Hipsell will protect your Personal Information in a manner that is consistent with and appropriate to the sensitivity of that Personal Information. Our handling of your Personal Information will respect its confidential nature at all times from the time of its collection until its ultimate disposal or destruction.</p>

      <h3>Accessing Your Personal Information</h3>
      <p>Access to your Personal Information held by Hipsell may be requested by contacting the Chief Privacy Officer in writing. We will respond to any access request within thirty days of receiving your request. Any questions with regard to requesting access to Personal Information may be addressed to the Chief Privacy Officer. You are asked to provide us with any updates regarding any inaccurate or incomplete Personal Information. </p>

      <h3>Responsibility for Compliance with our Privacy Policy</h3>
      <p>Our Chief Privacy Officer is responsible for overseeing Hipsell’s compliance with this Policy and may be contacted at the following address:</p>
      <pre>Chief Privacy Officer
488 Wellington St. West
Suite 300
Toronto, Ontario
M5V1E3</pre>

      <h3>Questions or Concerns About Our Privacy Practices</h3>
      <p>Please address any questions or concerns about our compliance with this Policy or our privacy practices generally to the Chief Privacy Officer.</p>
      <p>If you remain unsatisfied after discussing the matter with our Chief Privacy Officer, please contact the Privacy Commissioner of Canada at www.privcom.gc.ca or at the following address:</p>
